@@eThe Scorched Wastes: Collapsed Administrative District@@N

@@yBureau of Eastern Routes, Historical Threat Division@@N
@@dFiled under: Institutional Failure, Undead Persistence, Cautionary Record@@N

Our older ledgers refer to this region as the @@yMeridian Intake March@@N:
a managed corridor of toll pavilions, cistern regulators, and charter
stations. We held tariff agreements with the Intake offices. Our
clerks exchanged correspondence with their clerks. We recognized them
as @@ecolleagues in administration@@N.

They are all dead now. Some of them are still working.

The @@rNinth Meridian Rite@@N exceeded institutional competence in ways
our Bureau has classified as @@da cascading administrative failure of
the first order@@N. Heat surged through channels meant for water. The
sustained @@rburn wave@@N glassed dunes, collapsed structures, and
produced @@rundead administrative persistence@@N.

The @@yCharter Remnants@@N unsettle our clerks most. Descendants of
intake clerks and ration auditors -- some living survivalists, others
@@dundead functionaries still demanding documents and issuing
citations@@N before attacking when proper paperwork is not produced.
They stamp, witness, seal, and @@rkill@@N.

The Reckoning faction has circulated this in broadsheets: @@d"What
separates a Midgaard gate clerk from a Wastes revenant? The
revenant's institution collapsed. Ours has not. Yet."@@N The Continuity
faction finds this offensive. The Bureau finds it @@rtechnically
precise@@N.

The @@rDune Host Reavers@@N inherited route knowledge from ruined intake
records, hoarding water containers and legal tablets equally. The
@@dSynod Eclipse Cells@@N stage mock tribunals and witness-burning rites.
Both are parasites on a dead host's nervous system. Below them,
@@efaultline entities@@N manifest near dry governor mechanisms -- our
advisories classify these as @@rhazard: environmental, origin:
institutional residue@@N.

The Wastes share a thermal origin with the @@ySaltglass Reach@@N. The
same pulse that created this burn scar propagated eastward at
attenuated intensity. We note this coupling in our risk models.

The final assessment line in every Bureau report reads the same:
@@yLaw persists after legitimacy dies.@@N @@rWater memory outlives water
presence.@@N Administrative tools become ritual weapons under scarcity.
This is not foreign. This is @@rfamiliar@@N. That is what makes it a
cautionary record of the highest priority.
